# ============================================================================
# TIPS & TRICKS
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. Hot-reload configuration:
#    killall -HUP staticwall
#
# 2. Run with auto-reload:
#    staticwall --watch --daemon
#
# 3. Test configuration before daemonizing:
#    staticwall -v
#
# 4. Use absolute paths if ~ doesn't work:
#    path /home/username/Pictures/wallpaper.png
#
# 5. Organize wallpapers in folders and use directory cycling:
#    mkdir -p ~/Pictures/Wallpapers/{Nature,Abstract,Space}
#    cycle ~/Pictures/Wallpapers/Nature
#
# 6. Check logs for errors:
#    journalctl --user -u staticwall.service -f
#
# 7. Different configs for different scenarios:
#    staticwall -c ~/.config/staticwall/work.vibe
#    staticwall -c ~/.config/staticwall/home.vibe
#
# 8. Recommended cycling durations:
#    - Quick:    300 (5 minutes)
#    - Moderate: 900 (15 minutes)
#    - Slow:    1800 (30 minutes)
#    - Hourly:  3600 (1 hour)
#
# 9. Directory cycling:
#    Just set path to a directory with trailing slash:
#    path ~/Pictures/Wallpapers/
#    This automatically loads all PNG and JPEG files
#    Much easier than listing files manually!
#
# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
#
# Problem: "Configuration file not found"
# Solution: Make sure this file is at ~/.config/staticwall/config.vibe
#
# Problem: "Failed to parse VIBE config"
# Solution: Check for mismatched braces { } and brackets [ ]
#
# Problem: Wallpaper not showing
# Solution: Verify the image file exists: ls -la ~/Pictures/wallpaper.png
#
# Problem: Monitor not recognized
# Solution: Check exact monitor name with: swaymsg -t get_outputs
#
# Problem: Wallpapers not cycling
# Solution: Ensure duration > 0 and cycle array is populated
#
